<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 3:14PM ADT  by NWS San Juan</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Ponce, Morovis,
Orocovis, Adjuntas, Yauco, Villalba, Jayuya, and Penuelas
Municipalities through 315 PM AST...
At 211 PM AST, a strong thunderstorm was over Jayuya, Villalba and
Ponce. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
